.TH MULTIFLEXI\-HOUSEKEEPER 8 "June 2026" "multiflexi-housekeeper 1.0.0" "MultiFlexi"
.SH NAME
multiflexi\-housekeeper \- periodic maintenance for the MultiFlexi platform
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B multiflexi\-housekeeper
.RB [ \-\-dry\-run | \-n ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B multiflexi\-housekeeper
performs a set of housekeeping duties to keep the MultiFlexi ecosystem
running flawlessly. It is normally invoked once per hour by the
.B multiflexi\-housekeeper.timer
systemd timer unit, but can also be run on demand or as a long-running
daemon (see
.BR DAEMON ).
.PP
The following duties are executed in order:
.TP
.B 1. StaleTaskFinalization
Marks
.I open
or
.I running
Tasks whose scheduling window has already expired. Tasks with zero
attempts become
.IR missed ;
tasks with at least one attempt become
.IR failed .
Provides a safety net when the scheduler daemon is down.
.TP
.B 2. OrphanedJobCleanup
Calls
.B Scheduler::cleanupOrphanedJobs()
and
.B purgeBrokenQueueRecords()
to remove jobs with missing company or runtemplate references and broken
schedule queue entries. Also removes ghost jobs (unstarted, no queue
entry) older than
.BR MULTIFLEXI_HOUSEKEEPER_STALE_JOB_AGE .
.TP
.B 3. ScheduleIntegrity
Calls
.B Scheduler::initializeScheduling()
and resets stale
.I next_schedule
timestamps on RunTemplates that have no corresponding pending job, so
the scheduler daemon re-picks them up on its next tick.
.TP
.B 4. DataRetentionCleanup
Enforces GDPR data retention policies. Delegates to
.I MultiFlexi\eDataRetention\eRetentionService
when
.B multiflexi\-web
is installed; otherwise uses a built-in pass that reads the
.I data_retention_policies
table and applies
.I hard_delete
or
.I soft_delete
to expired rows.
.TP
.B 5. DiskTempFileCleanup
Removes orphaned temporary result files from the MultiFlexi temp
directory that are older than
.B MULTIFLEXI_HOUSEKEEPER_TMP_AGE_HOURS
hours and not referenced by any currently-running job.
.TP
.B 6. LogPruning
Deletes the oldest rows from the
.I log
table, keeping at most
.B MULTIFLEXI_HOUSEKEEPER_LOG_KEEP
records. Runs after all other duties so their log messages survive.
.TP
.B 7. RuntemplateCounterRecalc
Recalculates
.I successfull_jobs_count
and
.I failed_jobs_count
on all RunTemplates from the surviving job records. Corrects drift
caused by data retention deletions.
.TP
.B 8. CredentialHealthCheck
Calls
.B checkAvailability()
on the prototype of each credential assigned to an active RunTemplate.
Credentials returning
.I Misconfigured
are logged as warnings so operators can act before a job is blocked at
runtime.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run , \ \-n
Simulate all duties without making any database writes or filesystem
changes. Logs show what
.I would
be affected. Translates to
.B MULTIFLEXI_HOUSEKEEPER_DRY_RUN=true
internally.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
Configuration is read from
.I /etc/multiflexi/multiflexi.env
(or a
.I .env
file one level above the script).
.TP
.B DB_CONNECTION
Database driver:
.BR mysql ", " pgsql ", " sqlite " (default: mysql)"
.TP
.B DB_HOST
Database host (default:
.BR localhost )
.TP
.B DB_PORT
Database port
.TP
.B DB_DATABASE
Database name
.TP
.B DB_USERNAME
Database user
.TP
.B DB_PASSWORD
Database password
.TP
.B APP_DEBUG
Set to
.B true
to enable verbose console logging.
.TP
.B MULTIFLEXI_DAEMONIZE
Set to
.B true
to run in daemon mode (loop). Default:
.B false
(run once and exit, driven by the systemd timer).
.TP
.B MULTIFLEXI_HOUSEKEEPER_DRY_RUN
Set to
.B true
to simulate all duties without making changes. Default:
.BR false .
.TP
.B MULTIFLEXI_HOUSEKEEPER_CYCLE_PAUSE
Seconds to sleep between cycles in daemon mode. Default:
.BR 3600 .
.TP
.B MULTIFLEXI_HOUSEKEEPER_LOG_KEEP
Maximum number of rows to keep in the
.I log
table. Default:
.BR 100000 .
.TP
.B MULTIFLEXI_HOUSEKEEPER_TMP_AGE_HOURS
Minimum age in hours before orphaned temp files are deleted. Default:
.BR 24 .
.TP
.B MULTIFLEXI_HOUSEKEEPER_STALE_JOB_AGE
Minutes after which an unstarted, unscheduled job is considered orphaned.
Default:
.BR 60 .
.TP
.B MULTIFLEXI_HOUSEKEEPER_SKIP_DUTIES
Comma-separated list of duty class names to skip (short name without
namespace), e.g.\&
.IR "CredentialHealthCheck,LogPruning" .
.TP
.B MULTIFLEXI_HOUSEKEEPER_CREDENTIAL_CHECK
Set to
.B false
to disable the CredentialHealthCheck duty entirely. Default:
.BR true .
.TP
.B ZABBIX_SERVER
.TQ
.B ZABBIX_HOST
Enable Zabbix logging (same as other MultiFlexi daemons).
.SH DAEMON
To run as a continuous daemon rather than via the systemd timer:
.PP
.RS
.nf
MULTIFLEXI_DAEMONIZE=true multiflexi-housekeeper
.fi
.RE
.PP
Or enable daemon mode in
.I /etc/multiflexi/multiflexi.env
and use the service unit:
.PP
.RS
.nf
systemctl start multiflexi-housekeeper.service
.fi
.RE
.SH TIMER
The recommended deployment is via the systemd timer, which fires hourly
with up to 5 minutes of random jitter and catches up missed runs on boot
.RB ( Persistent=true ):
.PP
.RS
.nf
systemctl enable multiflexi-housekeeper.timer
systemctl start  multiflexi-housekeeper.timer
systemctl list-timers multiflexi-housekeeper
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run ad-hoc without waiting for the timer:
.PP
.RS
.nf
systemctl start multiflexi-housekeeper.service
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
All duties completed (individual errors are logged but do not change the
exit code).
.TP
.B 1
Another instance is already running, or the database is unavailable
after retries.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/multiflexi/multiflexi.env
Runtime environment configuration.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/multiflexi-housekeeper/housekeeper.php
Main PHP entry point.
.TP
.I /tmp/multiflexi-housekeeper.pid
PID lock file preventing concurrent runs.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR multiflexi-scheduler (8),
.BR multiflexi-executor (8)
.SH AUTHOR
Vítězslav Dvořák <info@vitexsoftware.cz>
